**Declaring and Printing an Integer Variable**

Here is an example in Python:

```python
# Declare a variable of type integer and assign it the value 10
my_integer: int = 10

# Print the variable's value
print(my_integer)
```

When you run this code, it will output: `10` 

This code can be written in other programming languages as well. Here are a few examples:

### Java
```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Declare a variable of type integer and assign it the value 10
        int myInteger = 10;

        // Print the variable's value
        System.out.println(myInteger);
    }
}
```

### C++
```cpp
#include <iostream>

int main() {
    // Declare a variable of type integer and assign it the value 10
    int myInteger = 10;

    // Print the variable's value
    std::cout << myInteger << std::endl;

    return 0;
}
```

### C#
```csharp
using System;

class Program {
    static void Main() {
        // Declare a variable of type integer and assign it the value 10
        int myInteger = 10;

        // Print the variable's value
        Console.WriteLine(myInteger);
    }
}
```
